## THE LOOP

```
REPEAT:
  1. PICK TICKET     -> Fetch top card from Trello "To Do" list
  2. /ticket FLOW    -> Implement (read .claude/commands/ticket.md and follow it)
  3. /temper FLOW    -> Review   (read .claude/commands/temper.md and follow it)
  4. /git-commit     -> Commit   (read .claude/commands/git-commit.md and follow it)
  5. /golive FLOW    -> Deploy   (read .claude/commands/golive.md and follow it)
  6. LOG RESULT      -> Append to ticket_summary.md
  7. NEXT TICKET     -> Go back to step 1
```

If at ANY point a genuine business question arises that cannot be answered from:
- `qictrader-backend-rs/docs/intended-entity-state-machines.md`
- `qictrader-backend-rs/docs/as-built-state-machines.md`
- The Trello card comments
- Plain logic and existing code patterns

Then: **LOG the question** to `ticket_questions.md`, mark the ticket as PARKED in `ticket_summary.md`, and **move to the next ticket**. Do NOT stop the pipeline.

